div.div:
This top-level FPGA module operates the Pmod HYGRO to obtain sensor readings,
converts these readings to ASCII data and text, and then outputs the ASCII data on
the UART TX and the ASCII text on the Pmod CLS LCD. The switches select the
one possible operational mode: Stream Measurements to Display. The driver for the
Pmod HYGRO is hardcoded to configure the HDC1080 to stream both Temperature
and Relative Humidity sensor readings in one bus read operation.
The color LEDs LD0, LD1, LD2, LD3 display information as to whether the sensor is
being operated, as well as which display format is being output to the LCD and
Terminal.
The Pmod CLS is selected to operate with SPI output and no SPI input, even though
the Pmod CLS additionally supports UART and I2C modes.
Switch 0 controls the program to run or stop running. Buttons 0, 1, 2, 3 are pressed
to select one of five different display formats to be applied to the ASCII text lines
displayed on the Pmod CLS LCD and the UART terminal.
